      ParkingSpot addVehicle(Vehicle v)
      Adds a vehicle to the parking lot.
      boolean allocate(ParkingRights type, int capacity)
      Allocates new parking spots of a certain type Note: They will all be allocated in linear order after the current spots already in the parking lot For example, an allocation of 5 spots on a parking with already 20 spots will get numbered 21-26 Note: Parking spots can only be of one type Note: Allocation of a type that already exists is allowed but their spots may not be consecutive to the old allocation For example, handicap spots could be #10-20 and #40-60 due to multiple allocations
      boolean removeVehicle(Vehicle v)
      Removes a vehicle from the parking lot

      • allocate

        public boolean allocate(ParkingRights type,
               int capacity)
        Allocates new parking spots of a certain type Note: They will all be allocated in linear order after the current spots already in the parking lot For example, an allocation of 5 spots on a parking with already 20 spots will get numbered 21-26 Note: Parking spots can only be of one type Note: Allocation of a type that already exists is allowed but their spots may not be consecutive to the old allocation For example, handicap spots could be #10-20 and #40-60 due to multiple allocations
        Parameters:
        type - - The type of spot
        capacity - - The number of those spots to create
        Returns:
        whether or not the allocation was successful

      • addVehicle

        public ParkingSpot addVehicle(Vehicle v)
        Adds a vehicle to the parking lot. It will add it to the most efficient location based on its type. Note: This method should not be called outside from the Vehicle class.
        Parameters:
        v - - The vehicle to add
        Returns:
        the Parking Spot where the vehicle was parked. Will return null if no spots were found.

      • removeVehicle

        public boolean removeVehicle(Vehicle v)
        Removes a vehicle from the parking lot
        Parameters:
        v - - The vehicle to remove
        Returns:
        whether or not the vehicle was removed successfully (will only fail if it was not there in the first place)
